==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impermeable
<hw>Im*per"me*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>permeable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>imperm⟦eacute⟧able</ets>, L. <ets>impermeabilis</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Not permeable; not permitting passage, as of a fluid. through its
substance; impervious; impenetrable; <as>as, India rubber is
<ex>impermeable</ex> to water and to air</as>.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Im*per"me*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Im*per"me*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impermissible</ent>⟦br⟧
